    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>53 W. 42<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> St<lb/>
                Nov. 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 5636<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd &#38; Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>The perusal of your<lb/> remarks on the Ritual Question act II<lb/> has left so agreeable an impression<lb/> on my mind&#44; that I cannot forbear<lb/> though only a lay man.  Expressing<lb/> to you&#44; my deep gratification and<lb/> pleasure.<lb/></p>
            <p>You have therein spoken<lb/> words and taken a position&#44; which<lb/> will find a ready response in the breasts and heads of thousands of<lb/> conservatives.<lb/></p>
            <p>Wold to Heaven those<lb/> Golden words had been spoken<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>twenty five years sooner&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>How much good might they<lb/> not have done&#33;  How much<lb/> Evil&#44; might they not have prevented&#33;<lb/></p>
            
            <p>It is however not yet too<lb/> late&#44; if the Ministers of the different<lb/> congregations will now go to<lb/> work unitedly.  Acting with<lb/> all possible circumspection&#45;&#45;<lb/>but without unnecessary delay.<lb/>  Every day is of importance.<lb/>  The unfortunate prejudices<lb/> existing between different nationalities<lb/> have been too long fostered&#33;<lb/>  War is made for trifles&#59; Principles<lb/> are <sic>oerlooked</sic>&#33;<lb/></p>
            
            <p>Let me pray you then<lb/> dear sir to stand firm<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>upon the ground you have<lb/> taken&#59; and soon I trust<lb/> you will find ardent<lb/> supporters and numerous<lb/> advocates&#44; in your just and<lb/> pious efforts.<lb/></p>
            
            <p>Trusting you will pardon<lb/> this intrusion for the sake of its motive&#44; I am<lb/> dear sir&#44; with kindest and<lb/> highest personal regard<lb/></p>
            <p>Very truly your&#39;s<lb/>
            De Mark Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            
            <p>Revd. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
            Philada<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
